# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BCP + Finance District integration — environment variables
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# These variables configure the Finance District-backed BCP examples.
# For the standalone BCP examples (no Finance District), see ../../.env.example
#
# Finance District developer docs: https://developers.fd.xyz

# ── Prism (seller-side settlement) ────────────────────────────────
#
# Your Prism API key ties this server to a Prism Console project.
# The project controls which chains and tokens are accepted, where
# settlement funds land, and delivers webhooks on each payment.
#
# Get your key: https://console.fd.xyz
# Docs: https://developers.fd.xyz/prism/sdk/typescript/express
PRISM_API_KEY=your_prism_api_key_from_console.fd.xyz

# Optional: override the Prism gateway URL (defaults to production)
PRISM_BASE_URL=https://prism-gw.fd.xyz

# ── Seller identity ────────────────────────────────────────────────
SELLER_ORG_ID=dataseller-co

# Price Prism presents in the HTTP 402 challenge.
# In production, derive this from the negotiated BCP QUOTE price.
DEAL_AMOUNT=$2.00

# ── Buyer identity ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
BUYER_ORG_ID=buyercorp

# ── Agent Wallet (buyer-side signing) ─────────────────────────────
#
# Agent Wallet authenticates via District Pass (email OTP) — there is
# no API key or private key to set here. The fdx CLI manages tokens in
# the OS credential store after you authenticate:
#
#   npm install -g @financedistrict/fdx
#   fdx register --email you@example.com
#   fdx verify --code XXXXXXXX   # 8-digit OTP sent to your inbox
#
# Docs: https://developers.fd.xyz/agent-wallet/ai-integration/cli
#
# BUYER_EVM_PRIVATE_KEY is NOT required when using Agent Wallet —
# the private key stays inside the TEE. You can still set it as a
# fallback for the standalone examples.
#
# BUYER_EVM_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...

# ── Network ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
NETWORK=base-sepolia
SELLER_PORT=3001
SELLER_URL=http://localhost:3001

# ── Currency ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# USDC is the default. Set to FDUSD to use Finance District's native
# stablecoin. FDUSD is supported by Agent Wallet on BSC, Ethereum,
# and Arbitrum. Ensure your Agent Wallet holds FDUSD on one of these
# chains and that your Prism project accepts FDUSD.
#
# Supported tokens and chains:
#   https://developers.fd.xyz/prism/production/network-support
CURRENCY=USDC
# CURRENCY=FDUSD

# ── Escrow contract ────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Still required — the buyer locks funds in the BCPEscrow contract on
# COMMIT. The seller's escrow release is handled by Prism when x402
# payment verifies, so the seller no longer needs a funded EVM wallet
# for gas.
BCP_ESCROW_CONTRACT_ADDRESS=0x...

# ── Optional: seller EVM key ───────────────────────────────────────
# Required only for the standard seller (examples/seller-server.ts).
# Not needed when using Prism — Prism's facilitator handles on-chain
# settlement without the seller signing transactions.
#
# SELLER_EVM_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...
